//Kiv <p>Kivorn the Teleri</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubryn5287.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bryn5287</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/22/02 8:00:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=837.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Deviant, evolution, get over it?</span><hr size=1> The openness of homosexuality has gone up and down over the centuries.<br>
Certainly ancient Greece celebrated homosexualty. Plato went so far as to<br>
describe the love of men to men as a higher love then men to women. There<br>
is evidence that Alexander the Great's elite cavalry unit &quot;the Companions&quot; <br>
was openly homosexual.<br>
<br>
I have a personal theory about the acceptance of certain behaviors. I believe<br>
that anything that is a positive survival trait starts out as a smart thing to do<br>
which over several generations becomes habit and then dogma. In farming<br>
societies, having kids is important so as to keep the farm going. Kids are<br>
your old age pension (i.e. working the farm so as to feed you while you help<br>
in less back breaking ways). Homosexuality would not be the best survival<br>
tactic for such societies. <br>
<br>
Robert Silverberg made an observation in his &quot;Book of Skulls&quot; which I thought<br>
was interesting. Silverberg observed that homosexuality is more accepted in<br>
urban cultures and incest in rural (incest due to the distances between families<br>
and the natural tendancy for kids to &quot;experiment&quot;). Interesting idea but I have<br>
no idea if its true of not.<br>
<br>
As for the idea that there is an &quot;increase in freedom to live as you want&quot;, I am not<br>
certain that is correct. I think some things are more accepted and some things less.<br>
The targets of bigotry and intolerance have shifted over the last 50 years but<br>
I don't think society is any more tolerant then it was before.<br>
<br>
Good Cheer,<br>
Brynie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uafierra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Afierra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/22/02 8:09:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=837.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Deviant, evolution, get over it?</span><hr size=1> Well I will be one to admit that outside of the game, I use the word &quot;gay&quot; quite a bit.  I tend to not use it in game/msg boards as people can't read your face as you say it (for the true meaning of what you meant by gay) nor can they accurately(sp?) interpret whether or not it was a directly prejudice towards their sexuality.<br>
